You can install desktop environment on Forsaken Linux

to install

For gnome doas apt install task-gnome-desktop
For kde doas apt install task-kde-desktop

after install run doas rm -rf /usr/share/desktop-base

You can also install other desktop environment

you must check ls /usr/share/desktop-base
if there is /usr/share/desktop-base run doas rm -rf /usr/share/desktop-base then doas apt-mark hold desktop-base

run sudo to check if sudo is installed if sudo is installed remove it again using doas apt purge sudo then doas apt autoremove

Note if the wallpaper is just plain color for example gnome having a blue in debian without desktop base you can change with default wallpaper
